                  <desc>Columetric layout of text: <locus target="#115v" facs="116">fols. 115v, </locus> (Ps. 150); <locus target="#125v #126r" facs="126">125v, 126r</locus> (tenth biblical canticle)</desc>
                  </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d1"><locus target="#155v" facs="156">Fol. 155v</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1082Angel">Angel</ref> with <term key="sword" ana="#sword"/> and scabbard. Caption in pencil next to wing: <q>“Saint Michael. . .[illegible]”</q>  Caption on <locus target="#156r" facs="156">fol. 156r</locus> is the likely original caption: “Who is this? Saint Michael</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d2"><locus target="#156r" facs="156">Fol. 156r</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1005Crucifixion">Crucifixion of Jesus</ref>,Crude drawing in pencil of Jesus on the Cross</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d3">
                      Decorative designs: <locus target="#1r #30r #37v #43r #52r #63r #71r #76r #88v #100r #103v #109v #116r #129v #137v #138r #155r" facs="001 030 038 043 052 063 071 076 089 100 104 110 116 130 138 155">folss. 1r, 30r, 37v, 43r, 52r, 63r, 71r, 76r, 88v, 100r, 103v, 109v, 116r, 129v, 137v, 138r, 155r, </locus> (ḥaräg);
                      <locus target="#6v #13r #20r" facs="007 013 020">6v, 13r, 20r</locus> (a line of alternating red and black dots)
                    </decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                    <list>
                      <item xml:id="e1">
                      <desc>
                      <locus target="#57v" facs="058">Fol. 57v</locus> A small cross in the margin marks the midpoint of the psalms.
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="a1">
                      <desc>
                      <locus target="#156r" facs="156">Fol. 156r</locus> to the right of the cross: Note from a student of Ge’ez
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e2">
                      <desc>
                      <locus target="#156r" facs="156">Fol. 156r</locus>, to the right of the cross: Note from a student of Ge’ez
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e3">
                      <desc>
                      <locus target="#156v" facs="157">Fol. 156v</locus> scrawls
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e4">
                      <desc>
                      words of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#10r #18v #31r #39r" facs="010 019 031 039">folss. 10r, 18v, 31r, 39r, </locus>, etc.);
                      and lines of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#55v #72r #153v" facs="056 072 154">55v, 72r, 153v, </locus>);
                      erasure markings are visible (<locus target="#66r #80v #84v" facs="066 081 085">66r, 80v, 84v, </locus>, etc.);
                      text has been removed (e.g., <locus target="#10r #17r #58r" facs="010 017 059">10r, 17r, 58r</locus>)
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e5">
                      <desc>
                      <locus target="#2v" facs="003"> f. 2v, line 25</locus><locus target="#16v" facs="017"> f. 16v, line 6</locus>: text has a line above and below to signal its erasure to correct homoeoteleuton
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e6">
                        <desc>
                          The scribe’s chosen aspect ratio for the codex combined with the script size forces the scribe to complete the line of text above or below the end of the line
                          (throughout). But, where the line of text is still too long, the scribe reduces the font size at the end of lines to avoid having to go onto the next line (throughout)
                        </desc>
                      </item>
                    </list>
                  </additions>
